<subSubSection id="70E51A85FFB62562FF4BAD74A84CCEB0" lastPageId="42" lastPageNumber="43" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" type="description">
<paragraph id="3840490EFFB62561FF4BAD74A8DAC8FC" blockId="41.[151,1437,1495,2027]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis id="0A8B951CFFB62561FF4BAD74AD94C900" bold="true" box="[199,419,1567,1594]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Description. Male.</emphasis>
Whole fly as 
<figureCitation id="A0C4558BFFB62561FDB2AD4BAEAAC900" box="[574,669,1567,1594]" captionStart="FIGURES 255–260" captionStartId="42.[151,264,1884,1909]" captionTargetBox="[209,1376,456,1857]" captionTargetId="figure@42.[209,1378,452,1858]" captionTargetPageId="42" captionText="FIGURES 255–260. Megaselia pereensis n. sp. male. 255, whole fly; 256, frons; 257, detail of frons; 258, postpedicel; 259, palp; 260, side of thorax. Scale bars 20 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573442" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3573442/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Fig. 255</figureCitation>
, Frons as 
<figureCitation id="A0C4558BFFB62561FC80AD4BAF5BC900" box="[780,876,1567,1594]" captionStart="FIGURES 255–260" captionStartId="42.[151,264,1884,1909]" captionTargetBox="[209,1376,456,1857]" captionTargetId="figure@42.[209,1378,452,1858]" captionTargetPageId="42" captionText="FIGURES 255–260. Megaselia pereensis n. sp. male. 255, whole fly; 256, frons; 257, detail of frons; 258, postpedicel; 259, palp; 260, side of thorax. Scale bars 20 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573442" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3573442/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Fig. 256</figureCitation>
, with very fine microtrichia on most of frons (
<figureCitation id="A0C4558BFFB62561FAE3AD4BACF2C964" captionStart="FIGURES 255–260" captionStartId="42.[151,264,1884,1909]" captionTargetBox="[209,1376,456,1857]" captionTargetId="figure@42.[209,1378,452,1858]" captionTargetPageId="42" captionText="FIGURES 255–260. Megaselia pereensis n. sp. male. 255, whole fly; 256, frons; 257, detail of frons; 258, postpedicel; 259, palp; 260, side of thorax. Scale bars 20 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573442" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3573442/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Fig. 257</figureCitation>
). Cheek with 4 bristles and jowl with 2 that are longer and more robust. Postpedicels without SPS vesicles and as 
<figureCitation id="A0C4558BFFB62561FF3BAD03AD2EC9B8" box="[183,281,1639,1666]" captionStart="FIGURES 255–260" captionStartId="42.[151,264,1884,1909]" captionTargetBox="[209,1376,456,1857]" captionTargetId="figure@42.[209,1378,452,1858]" captionTargetPageId="42" captionText="FIGURES 255–260. Megaselia pereensis n. sp. male. 255, whole fly; 256, frons; 257, detail of frons; 258, postpedicel; 259, palp; 260, side of thorax. Scale bars 20 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573442" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3573442/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Fig. 258</figureCitation>
. Palps as 
<figureCitation id="A0C4558BFFB62561FE06AD03ADDBC9B8" box="[394,492,1639,1666]" captionStart="FIGURES 255–260" captionStartId="42.[151,264,1884,1909]" captionTargetBox="[209,1376,456,1857]" captionTargetId="figure@42.[209,1378,452,1858]" captionTargetPageId="42" captionText="FIGURES 255–260. Megaselia pereensis n. sp. male. 255, whole fly; 256, frons; 257, detail of frons; 258, postpedicel; 259, palp; 260, side of thorax. Scale bars 20 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573442" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3573442/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Fig. 259</figureCitation>
. Proboscis with only a few short spinules below the labella. Thorax brown. With 3 notopleural bristles and no cleft in front of these. Mesopleuron with numerous small hairs and a single long bristle (
<figureCitation id="A0C4558BFFB62561FF2CADDBAD34C9F1" box="[160,259,1712,1739]" captionStart="FIGURES 255–260" captionStartId="42.[151,264,1884,1909]" captionTargetBox="[209,1376,456,1857]" captionTargetId="figure@42.[209,1378,452,1858]" captionTargetPageId="42" captionText="FIGURES 255–260. Megaselia pereensis n. sp. male. 255, whole fly; 256, frons; 257, detail of frons; 258, postpedicel; 259, palp; 260, side of thorax. Scale bars 20 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573442" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3573442/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Fig. 260</figureCitation>
). Scutellum with an anterior pair of small hairs and a posterior pair of bristles. Abdominal tergites brown (
<figureCitation id="A0C4558BFFB62561FF2CADBFACC9C9D5" box="[160,254,1748,1775]" captionStart="FIGURES 261–271" captionStartId="43.[151,264,1902,1927]" captionTargetBox="[211,1374,182,1876]" captionTargetId="figure@43.[208,1379,181,1876]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="FIGURES 261–271. Megaselia pereensis n. sp. male. 261, left face of abdomen; 262, tergite 6; 263, left face of hypopygium; 264, left face of epandrium and anal tube; 265, left face of hypandrium; 266, left face of penis complex; 267, right face of epandrium and anal tube; 268, segments 1 and 2 of front tarsus; 269, hind femur; 270, wing and haltere; 271, base of wing. Scale bars 20 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573444" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3573444/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Fig. 261</figureCitation>
) with numerous small hairs that are only a little longer at the rear of T6 (
<figureCitation id="A0C4558BFFB62561FBA8ADBFA8B1C9D5" box="[1060,1158,1748,1775]" captionStart="FIGURES 261–271" captionStartId="43.[151,264,1902,1927]" captionTargetBox="[211,1374,182,1876]" captionTargetId="figure@43.[208,1379,181,1876]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="FIGURES 261–271. Megaselia pereensis n. sp. male. 261, left face of abdomen; 262, tergite 6; 263, left face of hypopygium; 264, left face of epandrium and anal tube; 265, left face of hypandrium; 266, left face of penis complex; 267, right face of epandrium and anal tube; 268, segments 1 and 2 of front tarsus; 269, hind femur; 270, wing and haltere; 271, base of wing. Scale bars 20 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573444" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3573444/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Fig. 262</figureCitation>
). Venter brown, and with hairs on segments 3–6. Hypopygium as 
<figureCitation id="A0C4558BFFB62561FDD7AD93AECFC828" box="[603,760,1784,1810]" captionStart="FIGURES 261–271" captionStartId="43.[151,264,1902,1927]" captionTargetBox="[211,1374,182,1876]" captionTargetId="figure@43.[208,1379,181,1876]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="FIGURES 261–271. Megaselia pereensis n. sp. male. 261, left face of abdomen; 262, tergite 6; 263, left face of hypopygium; 264, left face of epandrium and anal tube; 265, left face of hypandrium; 266, left face of penis complex; 267, right face of epandrium and anal tube; 268, segments 1 and 2 of front tarsus; 269, hind femur; 270, wing and haltere; 271, base of wing. Scale bars 20 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573444" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3573444/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Figs 263–267</figureCitation>
. Legs brown. Fore tarsus basal 2 segments as 
<figureCitation id="A0C4558BFFB62561FB73AD93A96AC828" box="[1279,1373,1784,1810]" captionStart="FIGURES 261–271" captionStartId="43.[151,264,1902,1927]" captionTargetBox="[211,1374,182,1876]" captionTargetId="figure@43.[208,1379,181,1876]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="FIGURES 261–271. Megaselia pereensis n. sp. male. 261, left face of abdomen; 262, tergite 6; 263, left face of hypopygium; 264, left face of epandrium and anal tube; 265, left face of hypandrium; 266, left face of penis complex; 267, right face of epandrium and anal tube; 268, segments 1 and 2 of front tarsus; 269, hind femur; 270, wing and haltere; 271, base of wing. Scale bars 20 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573444" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3573444/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Fig. 268</figureCitation>
(segment 5 lost on both legs). Dorsal hair palisade of mid tibia extends about 0.72 times its length. Hairs below basal half of hind femur longer than those of anteroventral row of outer half (
<figureCitation id="A0C4558BFFB62561FC0FAC2BAFD1C861" box="[899,998,1856,1883]" captionStart="FIGURES 261–271" captionStartId="43.[151,264,1902,1927]" captionTargetBox="[211,1374,182,1876]" captionTargetId="figure@43.[208,1379,181,1876]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="FIGURES 261–271. Megaselia pereensis n. sp. male. 261, left face of abdomen; 262, tergite 6; 263, left face of hypopygium; 264, left face of epandrium and anal tube; 265, left face of hypandrium; 266, left face of penis complex; 267, right face of epandrium and anal tube; 268, segments 1 and 2 of front tarsus; 269, hind femur; 270, wing and haltere; 271, base of wing. Scale bars 20 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573444" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3573444/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Fig. 269</figureCitation>
). Hind tibia with a dozen differentiated posterodorsal hairs, without anterodorsals, and spinules of apical combs simple. Wings (
<figureCitation id="A0C4558BFFB62561FBFAAC0FA91EC844" box="[1142,1321,1892,1918]" captionStart="FIGURES 261–271" captionStartId="43.[151,264,1902,1927]" captionTargetBox="[211,1374,182,1876]" captionTargetId="figure@43.[208,1379,181,1876]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="FIGURES 261–271. Megaselia pereensis n. sp. male. 261, left face of abdomen; 262, tergite 6; 263, left face of hypopygium; 264, left face of epandrium and anal tube; 265, left face of hypandrium; 266, left face of penis complex; 267, right face of epandrium and anal tube; 268, segments 1 and 2 of front tarsus; 269, hind femur; 270, wing and haltere; 271, base of wing. Scale bars 20 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573444" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3573444/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Figs 270 &amp; 271</figureCitation>
